|CKBStreet Samurai|000

|CK0Street Samurai are cybernetic combat specialists whose Cortex OS links
signature implants into one platform. They earn guild experience through
Darkwind's shared battle progression, create and spend Edge, manage Heat, and
maintain their installed hardware.|000

|CK0Most active firmware remains usable at zero Edge. When Edge is available,
the Cortex automatically routes it into stronger damage, duration, shielding,
healing, or control effects. Specialized routines have their own Edge behavior,
explained through samhelp resources and samhelp <routine>.|000

|CK0Guild Level unlocks firmware and signature implants through GL16. Cortex
Rank continues through CR200 as long-term progression. The public contract
office is east of Fountain Court near Moongate Plaza; joining installs the
starter Cortex OS automatically.|000

|CK0Rin Kade operates the restricted guild clinic beyond the contract office.
Active members pay for signature hardware but receive covered installation,
extraction, and signature repair services. Samrepair is only for a corrupt or
incomplete guild installation, not normal onboarding.|000

|CKBStarting commands|000
|CK0dashboard - firmware version, Cortex, and implant diagnostic
samskills - routine unlocks, costs, and readiness
samstatus - compact combat and resource state
samxp - Guild Level, Cortex Rank, and GXP progress
samspam [verbose|brief|off] - implant activation message detail
samhelp start - first-deployment checklist and combat loop
samhelp commands - complete command and topic index|000

|CK0Use samhelp <routine> for focused firmware guidance. Samhelp resources,
firmware, hardware, maintenance, mon, contract, prices, and network explain the
guild's major systems and the decisions each one supports.|000
